ILLINOIS COAL: THE LEGACY OF AN INDUSTRIAL SOCIETY 
Cox, coal miner, discusses his experiences in the mines around Taylorville, Illinois: mine union wars, pit committeemen, mine superintendents, and "dirt gangs." He also discusses his family and childhood in Hamilton County, Illinois.1 tape, 90 mins., 36 pp.
Interview by Kevin Corley, 1986 
